[38.129076, "o", "s"]
[38.239259, "o", "t"]
[39.200094, "o", "\r\r\n"]
[39.200589, "o", "\r\nKnowledge base (6 topics):\r\n  \u001b[36magentOS-overview\u001b[0m — AgentOS: open-source AI agent, multi-channel, HAM memory, MIT\r\n  \u001b[36mham-memory\u001b[0m — HAM: 4-level compression, state machine routing, 400-token budget, 82% savings\r\n  \u001b[36mllm-routing\u001b[0m — Routing: cc:→Claude, g:→Gemini, auto=Gemini Flash classifies\r\n  \u001b[36mcli-commands\u001b[0m — CLI commands: /help /clear /model /skills /memory /exit\r\n  \u001b[36minstallation-quickstart\u001b[0m — Install: clone, npm install, add API key to .env, npm run build, npm run cli\r\n  \u001b[36mmcp-tools\u001b[0m — MCP: JSON-RPC 2.0 stdio + 4 builtins: web_fetch, bash, read_file, write_file\r\n"]
[39.200643, "o", "\r\n"]
[39.20068, "o", "\u001b[1G\u001b[0J\u001b[36m❯\u001b[0m \u001b[3G"]
[43.45695, "o", "How d"]
[43.457007, "o", "oes th"]
[43.457038, "o", "e HA"]
[43.457089, "o", "M mem"]
[43.457121, "o", "ory a"]
[43.457153, "o", "lg"]
[43.457634, "o", "orithm work exactly?"]
[44.424376, "o", "\r\r\n\r\n"]
[45.482516, "o", "HAM"]
[45.482758, "o", " (Hierarchical"]
[45.483168, "o", " Adaptive Memory) stores each topic at 4 compression levels. It uses a zero-"]
[45.491531, "o", "cost regex state machine to detect the conversation state (INTRO, PROBLEM, SOLUTION, DEEP_"]
[45.689162, "o", "DIVE, CTA, FEATURES, GENERAL). This state is then mapped to a specific retrieval depth. For example, routine questions might load only the L1 level"]
[45.88639, "o", " (35 tokens), while deep technical queries would load up to the L3 level (500+ tokens). The active memory is capped at 40"]
[46.134709, "o", "0 tokens and uses access-weighted pruning to manage memory usage. This approach achieves approximately 82% token savings compared to using the full conversation context naively.\r\n"]
[46.137078, "o", "\r\n\r\n\u001b[2m  ─\u001b[0m \u001b[32mgemini\u001b[0m\u001b[2m · 617↑ 139↓ tokens\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
